*alsa-utils-1.0.19-r1 (21 Feb 2009)

  21 Feb 2009; <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +files/alsasound-1.0.19-r1.initd,
  +alsa-utils-1.0.19-r1.ebuild:
  Incorporate changes suggested by Dennis <lindevel@gmx.net> to repair the
  module loading regexes after module-init-tools 3.6 broke them. Closes bug
  #258930.

*alsa-utils-1.0.19 (19 Jan 2009)

  19 Jan 2009; <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +files/alsasound-1.0.19.confd,
  +files/alsasound-1.0.19.initd, +alsa-utils-1.0.19.ebuild:
  Version bump, disabling the ill-advised automatic module unloading. Note
  that our recommendations have changed, you are encouraged to build your
  audio drivers into the kernels unless the device is hotpluggable or needs
  special parameters (such as model= for HD-Audio). Unloading did not work
  if the audio device prefix was not snd, as reported by chad heuschober
  <chad_ryan1@hotmail.com> in bug #175740. As Dieter Ries <clip2@gmx.de>
  reported in bug #253535 the modularisation of the HD-Audio driver meant
  that the fragile code handling this broke further as ordering was not
  taken into account.

  21 Dec 2008; nixnut <nixnut@gentoo.org> alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc wrt bug 245517

  20 Dec 2008; Ferris McCormick <fmccor@gentoo.org>
  alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  Sparc stable, Bug #245517.

  20 Dec 2008; Thomas Anderson <gentoofan23@gentoo.org>
  alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  stable amd64, bug 245517

  16 Dec 2008; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  Marking alsa-utils-1.0.17 ppc64 for bug 245517

  16 Dec 2008; Tobias Klausmann <klausman@gentoo.org>
  alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha, bug 245517

  16 Dec 2008; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #245517).

  15 Dec 2008; <ssuominen@gentoo.org> alsa-utils-1.0.17.ebuild:
  x86 stable wrt #245517

  14 Nov 2008; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  files/alsa-utils-1.0.11_rc2-nls.patch,
  files/alsa-utils-1.0.11_rc5-alsaconf-redirect.patch,
  files/alsa-utils-1.0.14-alsaconf-modules-update.patch:
  Replace the patches that has been submitted upstream with the actual patch
  from the git repository.

